# Code language: English only

**All source code and in-app user-facing text must be in English. Never write code, comments, or UI strings in French (or any other language) in the codebase.**

- **Comments**: English only (e.g. `// Plex code displayed inline`, not `// Code affiché inline`).
- **UI strings**: English only (labels, buttons, messages, placeholders). E.g. "Open plex.tv/link", "Code to enter on plex.tv/link", not "Ouvrir plex.tv/link", "Code à entrer".
- **Variable/function names**: English only.
- **Log messages**: English only.
- **Error messages shown to users**: English only.

Documentation (e.g. `docs/`, README) may be in French or English as needed for the audience; this rule applies to code and in-app text only.
